# Tailwind v4 Arbitrary Values — Known Limitations & Workarounds

## Core Problem

Tailwind v4 **cannot parse** arbitrary values containing commas or slashes inside `[...]` brackets. The parser interprets commas as value separators and slashes as modifier separators, causing the class to be silently dropped from the compiled CSS.

## Broken patterns — DO NOT USE

```jsx
// Commas inside clamp() — Tailwind v4 breaks
className="text-[clamp(1.8rem,4vw,2.8rem)]"

// Commas inside repeat() and minmax() — breaks
className="grid-cols-[repeat(auto-fit,minmax(240px,1fr))]"

// Slashes in aspect-ratio — breaks
className="aspect-[4/3]"
```

## Workarounds that DO NOT work

❌ `text-[clamp(1.8rem_4vw_2.8rem)]` — underscores NOT supported in TW4
❌ `@layer utilities { .my-class { ... } }` — TW4 reorders layers, ignores @layer
❌ `@layer components { .my-class { ... } }` — same problem

## Working solution: globals.css with !important

Move the CSS out of Tailwind's JIT scope entirely. Use `globals.css` with **tag selectors** and **!important** for maximum specificity:

```css
/* globals.css — fixes that TW4 arbitrary values can't handle */

@import "tailwindcss";

/* ── Typography overrides ── */
h1 {
  font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3.5rem) !important;
}
h2 {
  font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 2.2rem) !important;
}
h3 {
  font-size: clamp(1.1rem, 2vw, 1.5rem) !important;
}

/* ── Grid definitions ── */
@media (min-width: 640px) {
  .grid-cols-features {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(240px, 1fr));
  }
  .grid-cols-services {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
  }
}

/* ── Image overrides (tag + class selector for max specificity) ── */
img.process-step-img {
  max-width: 150px !important;
  width: 150px !important;
  height: auto !important;
  border-radius: 8px !important;
  display: block !important;
  margin-bottom: 12px !important;
}
```

## CSS Layer priority in Tailwind v4

Tailwind v4's `@import "tailwindcss"` internally uses:
```
@layer base, components, utilities;
```

Any CSS NOT in a `@layer` gets put into an anonymous layer that has **lower priority** than Tailwind's own `utilities` layer. The `!important` flag overrides this ordering. Tag selectors (`h1`, `img.process-step-img`) add specificity.

## When to use each approach

| Problem | Solution |
|---------|----------|
| H1/H2/H3 font sizes | Global CSS with `!important` + tag selector |
| Grid layouts (repeat, auto-fit) | Utility class in `globals.css`, use class name in JSX |
| Image sizes | Tag+class selector in `globals.css` with `!important` |
| Aspect ratios | Use `max-width` + `height: auto` instead of `aspect-ratio` |

## Build verification

After applying globals.css fixes, always verify the CSS rule exists in the built output:

```bash
docker run --rm nexa-paraguay:prod sh -c "grep 'clamp\|grid-cols-features\|process-step-img' /app/.next/static/chunks/*.css | head -5"
```
